This repository contains precomputed eigenvalue spectra of the
prolate-wave operator PW_λ — the CCM "educated guess" operator from
Section 7 of the Connes-Consani-Moscovici construction (the "Data") —
generated by the Xcelerator Toolkit
(https://github.com/TeamXcelerator/xcelerator-toolkit). For a given
parameter λ² (prime-cutoff), finite-difference grid size (N), and
working precision the Data are uniquely determined by the discretized
Sturm-Liouville eigenproblem and contain no additional proprietary
information.

Permission is granted to:
- Download and use the Data to accelerate reproduction of published
  Team Xcelerator findings or for academic research that cites this
  work and the associated publications
- Read, verify, and study the Data for educational purposes
- Cite this repository in academic publications with proper attribution

Permission is NOT granted to:
- Redistribute the Data as part of another dataset or product without
  explicit written permission
- Use the Data or anything derived from it for commercial purposes

The Data are provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. Every file
is structurally validated by the Xcelerator Toolkit on load
(eigenvalue count = N, ascending order, ground state ≈ 2π·λ² to within
a few percent, no NaN/Inf); consumers should rely on that validation
rather than assuming any file is correct.

